## Rules

### SEC-001: Authentication Requirements
severity: ERROR
scope: all API endpoints and service methods accessing protected resources
rule: All endpoints that access user data or perform state mutations MUST require authentication. Unauthenticated access to protected routes is prohibited.
threshold: min_password_length=12, max_session_minutes=60
example_correct: |
  @require_auth
  def get_user_profile(user_id: str) -> Response: ...
example_incorrect: |
  def get_user_profile(user_id: str) -> Response:
      # No auth check — prohibited

### SEC-002: Secret Management
severity: ERROR
scope: all source files and configuration
rule: Secrets, API keys, and credentials MUST NOT be hardcoded in source code or committed to version control. All secrets MUST be loaded from environment variables or a secrets manager.
threshold: min_password_length=12
example_correct: |
  api_key = os.environ["API_KEY"]
example_incorrect: |
  api_key = "sk-live-abc123"  # hardcoded — prohibited

### SEC-003: Input Validation
severity: ERROR
scope: all public API inputs and user-supplied data
rule: All user-supplied input MUST be validated and sanitized before use. SQL queries MUST use parameterized statements. HTML output MUST be escaped. Unvalidated input is prohibited.
threshold: max_session_minutes=60
example_correct: |
  cursor.execute("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = %s", (user_id,))
example_incorrect: |
  cursor.execute(f"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = {user_id}")  # SQL injection
